Mr Nyagah served in former president Daniel Moi's last cabinet. He was son of the late Jeremiah Nyagah, one of the ministers in Moi’s first cabinet.
Joe Nyagah vied for the presidency in the 2017 General Elections as an independent candidate. He had resigned as presidential advisor on regional integration and as chancellor of the Co-operative College citing frustrations caused by internal fighting within top Jubilee leaders.  



